Add new entries for the database to the Council Application Page

Run the <DBA_MaintenancePlan.Update SQL Server Central> Job on Source SQL Server Instance.

Disable all the DBA_Maintenance Plans jobs in the SQL Server Instance if all the Databases are candidate for decommissioning.

Update the Offline Date on Database Central - M903PRD1



/* Find the Server ID */
select Server_ID,Server_Name,Last_Modified_Date,Decommission_date from [Database_Central].[bcc].[MSSQL_server]
where server_Name = '<SQL Server Instance Name>'
/*Find the Database needs to be updated with offline date*/
select Database_Name,status,Last_Modified_Date,Database_Offline_Date from [Database_Central].[bcc].[MSSQL_Database]
where server_ID = <Server_ID> and Database_Name not in ('model','msdb','tempdb','master')
/*Update the Offline Date for specific Database*/
-- RUN THE BEGIN TRAN WITHOUT COMMIT
BEGIN TRAN 
UPDATE [Database_Central].[bcc].[MSSQL_Database]
SET Database_Offline_Date = getdate() -- or the date the Database being offline
WHERE SERVER_ID = <Server ID> and Database_Name = '<Database Name>'
COMMIT --  IF YOU SEE THE SAME EXPECTED AFFECTED ROW COUNT THAN ONLY RUN COMMIT ELSE RUN ROLLBACK
/*Verify the change */
select Database_Name,Database_Offline_Date,Last_Database_Backup_Date,Last_Modified_Date from [Database_Central].[bcc].[MSSQL_Database]
where server_ID = <Server ID> and status = 'OFFLINE' 
Run the <DBA_MaintenancePlan.Update SQL Server Central> Job on destination SQL Server Instance.

Update the Application name, System Code and Application Contact on Database Central - M903PRD1



use Database_Central
go
select s.Server_Name,d.Database_ID,d.Database_Name,d.Status,
d.Application_Name,d.Application_Contact,d.decommission_date
from bcc.MSSQL_Database d, Database_Central.bcc.MSSQL_Server s 
where d.Database_Name='<DATABASE_NAME>' and s.Environment='<ENVIRONMENT> '
and s.Server_ID = d.Server_ID
go
--Update the Application name, System Code and Application Contact
Update bcc.MSSQL_Database set Application_Name='<>',Application_Contact='<>',system_code='<>'
where Database_ID=<Database_ID>
go
